	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Hey, all:)<BR>
I'm a Ranger on Brell and have been fighting in SK lately and have seen Coloth Meadowgreen 3 times.  On the first occasion I got three friends to help and try to kill him.  Myself, a 25 Ranger, a 38 druid, a 28 bard, and a 22 druid all died trying to kill him:)  The bard's damage shield got him as he was killed:)  The druid was low mana though when we attacked.  When we go back tohis corpse he only looted a longbow.  Yes the same one sold by merchants.  About a week later I was hunting outside of Paw and took a brek to kite an avocet.  On my way back to the group at Paw I saw Coloth on track.  I told my group immediately and they told me to bring him over.  I told them that he destroy me before I'd get there so they headed to my loc.  I was off in the booneys of South Karana and they were having trouble finding me so I thought that since I had SoW I could pull him to my group for an ambush.  Ha!  Silly me!  He runs faster than SoW and hit me for, if I can remeber correctly, 90 points maxed out and VERY fast.  Didn't take long to leave me dead in the dirt.  But my faithful and wonderful group tracked him down and avenged my death:)  Thanks, guys:)  They were only 4 ranging from 24-30 with I think 3 pure casters and 1 tank (betheby!!:)))).  And they got him with no casualties.  And he dropped the Runed Oak Bow.  Xarius graciously gave me the bow:)  I can't thank you enough:)  I LOVE my bow and will never give it up...  EVER.  I know that's what I'd said about my Lupine Claw Gauntlets but I mean it this time so don't harass me:-P<BR>
    Oh, yeah.  About the third time I saw him it was actually later that night:)  I announced his presence cause I had no friends near zone at the time and a 43 enchanter came.  He had a 26 druid with him for heals and buffs.  I stayed to watch Coloth destroy both of them.  The enchanter looked like he knew what he was doing, but ya never can tell with those damned pure casters:)  (Just kidding, Maeldun, Blakk, Abinadi, Xarius, and everyone else I've forgotten at 2 o'clock in the morning:-P)  Then I watched a 35 Ranger and a 38 Mage try him.  I warned the Ranger cause we're kin, but would she listen?  :-P  Boom!  Dead Ranger:(  Woosh!  Evac Mage.  I cried and lamented for days and then got all the mid 20's groups at Paw to help:)  I dedicated the fight to all who had passed by his hand.  Like maybe 15 players, mostly tanks got him finally after 2-3 of us died.  I was one of the fallen and I'd asked if the bow could be given to Gweinea, the late 35 Ranger.  Raguk replied, &quot;Of course, for your death.&quot;  But then he said that when he checked the corpse all that was found was a regular old Longbow:(  Sorry Gweinea:(  Aaah, well.  Those are my Coloth stories:)  If you've gotten this far I'm sorry:)  Hehe  It's late.  I tend to Ramble on:)  See y'all later.<BR>
    Sorry about any of my dear friends I forgot to mention in this.  It really is very late and I have mono!:(  Actually not anymore but I still get relapses so, Ha!:-P<BR>
<BR>
Later, y'all.<BR>
<BR>
Ranger power!<BR>
Ancient Masters!<BR>
Wood Elves in leather!<BR>
<BR>
BTW I'm single and looking:)  I'm a very sexy Wood Elf Ranger in Ivy Etched:)  I'm looking for a sweet, curvacious Wood Elf or Erudite who enjoys long walks through the lush forests of the Greater Faydark, serene boat rides over the waters of Rathe, or frolicking across the lands of Norrath:)  Gimme a tell:)  <BR>
<BR>
(I'm a guy by the way:)  In EQ and RL...  Hehe)<BR>
